{
  "stem": "4963.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she-- my grandfather had died, and so she came to live with us right after her grand-- my grandfather died.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was Babushka, we used to call her, which is grandmother in Russian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so there wasn't morning when we wouldn't-- before going to school we would go over to her headquarters, where she lived.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She had her own bedroom and bathroom, a whole wing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we would kiss her hello, good morning, and the evening before we went to bed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] We would-- yeah, excuse me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We would immediately, before we went to bed, we would again go over and kiss her and say goodbye, you know, good night.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, my grandmother lived with us until she died 1939.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My parents were always respectful of her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she-- they always-- I never heard any cross words, you know, any-- any time, saying anything bad about my grandmother or anything criticizing her.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She was always, whatever Grandmother said, you know, we did it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In the home my father had three-- three sisters.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so the sisters would come to our house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a gathering place for everybody because my grandmother was there and, of course, my father was the only son as well.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I think a long time ago there was-- my father had a brother, but he died and no one ever spoke about him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I think he died-- not quite sure of what he died of.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it was some secret of disease or mental disease.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I'm not quite sure what it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now on my mother's side, my grandmother-- and my grandmother lived not far from us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They had a large bakery and so they were also very well-to-do.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
